# Floating Windows Configuration
#
# This file contains rules to make specific applications always open as floating
# windows instead of tiled windows.
#
# --- How to find an application's identifier ---
#
# 1. Open the application you want to make floating
# 2. Run this command in a terminal:
#      swaymsg -t get_tree | grep -i "app_id\|class"
# 3. Look for the app_id (Wayland apps) or class (X11 apps) of your application
#
# Alternatively, for a more focused search:
#      swaymsg -t get_tree | grep -Po '"(app_id|class)": *"\K[^"]*'
#
# --- Syntax ---
#
# for_window [app_id="APPLICATION_ID"] floating enable
# for_window [class="APPLICATION_CLASS"] floating enable
#
# You can also match by title or other criteria. See: man 5 sway
#
# --- Examples ---

# GNOME Calculator
for_window [app_id="org.gnome.Calculator"] floating enable

# Other common floating applications (uncomment to use):
